e story that everything in Vijayawada needs a certain level of influence and most of it has already been settled by the dominant ones (politically) and the well connected owing to various other reasons. Vijayawada has been declared as the grand capital of Andhra Pradesh by Mr. Chandrababu Naidu the Chief Minister of the state who plans to build it on the lines of Singapore.\n\nIn Vishakhapatnam the story seems to be slightly different with land still being available although at highly inflated prices that have quadrupled since the erstwhile state of Andhra Pradesh split into two. A number of companies have since then sprung up in the residual state of Andhra Pradesh (which goes by its parent name) that have been offering land at highly exorbitant rates.\n\nSome of these companies like Nivas properties are using novel methods like email marketing to target the NRI’s spread in the US and other countries, especially the large Telugu community which is spread across the US. Some of them go with a catch “Sea view from First floor (if constructed)!” Others measure the distance from the beach. 2000, 3000, 5000… You name it. Unfortunately to many of the fisherman communities living around, the distance is several hundreds of thousands of feet from this prized land, in spite of them living so close to it.\n\nThere is an intense competition playing out between Chandrababu Naidu the Chief Minister of Andhra Pradesh and K Chandrasekhar Rao the Chief Minister of Telangana that has excited the NRI’s living in the US from both Andhra Pradesh and Telangana. While K Chandrasekhar Rao popularly known as KCR plans to develop Hyderabad further on the lines of Istanbul in Turkey and Shanghai in China, Naidu is readying plans to transform Vijaywada into Singapore complete with a newly built skyline.\n\n&nbsp;','NRI’s creating a Real Estate Bubble in the New State of Andhra Pradesh?','','inherit','closed','closed','','282-autosave-v1','','','2015-12-22 07:59:29','2015-12-22 07:59:29','',282,'http://caltechsoft.com/rankprop/282-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(317,1,'2015-12-22 07:59:52','2015-12-22 07:59:52','Meanwhile the land broker is busy haggling with Srinivas who works in Dallas, USA about a couple of hundred rupees per square yard which he deems difficult to concede, especially given the fact that the piece of land is much closer to the highway. “They are selling like hotcake everywhere, everything closer to the heart of the city is already taken! Especially given the fact that you have to be politically connected to get some land around Vijayawada the new capital” says Babloo.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://image.indiaopines.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/NRI-REAL-ESTATE.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"599\" height=\"398\" />\r\n\r\nA number of sources have revealed the same story that everything in Vijayawada needs a certain level of influence and most of it has already been settled by the dominant ones (politically) and the well connected owing to various other reasons. Vijayawada has been declared as the grand capital of Andhra Pradesh by Mr. Chandrababu Naidu the Chief Minister of the state who plans to build it on the lines of Singapore.\r\n\r\nIn Vishakhapatnam the story seems to be slightly different with land still being available although at highly inflated prices that have quadrupled since the erstwhile state of Andhra Pradesh split into two. A number of companies have since then sprung up in the residual state of Andhra Pradesh (which goes by its parent name) that have been offering land at highly exorbitant rates.\r\n\r\nSome of these companies like Nivas properties are using novel methods like email marketing to target the NRI’s spread in the US and other countries, especially the large Telugu community which is spread across the US. Some of them go with a catch “Sea view from First floor (if constructed)!” Others measure the distance from the beach. 2000, 3000, 5000… You name it. Unfortunately to many of the fisherman communities living around, the distance is several hundreds of thousands of feet from this prized land, in spite of them living so close to it.\r\n\r\nThere is an intense competition playing out between Chandrababu Naidu the Chief Minister of Andhra Pradesh and K Chandrasekhar Rao the Chief Minister of Telangana that has excited the NRI’s living in the US from both Andhra Pradesh and Telangana. While K Chandrasekhar Rao popularly known as KCR plans to develop Hyderabad further on the lines of Istanbul in Turkey and Shanghai in China, Naidu is readying plans to transform Vijaywada into Singapore complete with a newly built skyline.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','NRI’s creating a Real Estate Bubble in the New State of Andhra Pradesh?','','inherit','closed','closed','','282-revision-v1','','','2015-12-22 07:59:52','2015-12-22 07:59:52','',282,'http://caltechsoft.com/rankprop/282-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(318,1,'2015-12-22 08:01:38','2015-12-22 08:01:38','<i>Since the search to find the new capital for Seemandhra is on, Guntur has also emerged as a strong contender. It seems that Guntur’s future is bright once the two states split.</i>\r\n\r\nSituated on the banks of Krishna river delta, Guntur is a centre for business and commerce of various industries, such as textile and agriculture industries. In recent years, the city has gained prominence due to its thriving spice industry. The long coastal line and highways in the city allows the traders to export their products to different parts of the country and the world.\r\n\r\nThe city is experiencing a lot of development in its infrastructure and transportation in the recent years. So, what lies ahead for the city of spices?\r\n\r\n<b>Real estate scenario </b>\r\n\r\nAccording to Magicbricks data, the current rates of apartment in the city are between Rs 3000- Rs 3500 per sq ft. A 2BHK apartment in Guntur having a 1000-1200 sq ft area costs between Rs 40-45 lakh. However, the rates in the outer areas of Guntur are comparatively less. However, owning a property in the outskirts of Guntur is quite cheaper as the starting price of a 2BHK apartment (1000-1200 sq ft area) in Gorantla is just Rs 20 lakh.\r\n\r\nWith a lot of private companies coming up in the city and setting up their offices here, market experts in the city expect a substantial amount of growth in the next five years. “There is availability of state land to set up government offices. Infrastructure in the city is good and we have excellent connectivity with other parts of Seemandhra,” says Siva, managing director of Sri Bala Krishna Construction, a local developer.\r\n\r\n“We are already seeing a positive growth in the real estate industry of the city. Real estate prices have risen up to 20 per cent in the last three months,” he adds.\r\n\r\nPeople who are investing in the properties are NRIs, people from other parts of state and a few local people. “Most of them are end users but now the investors too have started investing in the properties here,” says Siva.\r\n\r\nAn IT Park and a textile hub are already being set up near Guntur and thus are likely to draw in hundreds of jobs in the city. Moreover, government has proposed to build two new plans – Knowledge Park and Biotechnology Park.\r\n\r\n“Once the city starts providing more employment opportunities, people will migrate here from different parts of Seemandhra, all these people are definitely going to invest in the properties here,” says Naidu Rao, marketing head of SVR Developers.\r\n\r\n<b>Infrastructure </b>\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to transportation, Guntur is well-connected to all the major cities such as Chennai, Kolkata, Hyderabad, Vijaywada, Tenali, Kurnool, Bellary and all other parts of Seemandhra. Government has also laid plans to improve the two main railway stations of the city – one in Arundelpet and the other in Railpet. The international airport that is being planned in Vijaywada is just 45 km away from the city.\r\n\r\n“Good connectivity, availability of schools, colleges, hospitals, availability of water, industries, coast; Guntur has all major ingredients that a city needs to grow. The future of the city seems promising,” adds Rao.\r\n\r\nKrishna River provides ample water to the citizens of the city and all the industries that are situated in the area. Some parts of Seemandhra, especially the areas under Rayalaseema, have a huge water shortage. Thus, availability of water in Guntur is attracting more industries to the city.','Guntur’s future looks promising post Telangana','','inherit','closed','closed','','284-revision-v1','','','2015-12-22 08:01:38','2015-12-22 08:01:38','',284,'http://caltechsoft.com/rankprop/284-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(319,1,'2015-12-22 16:56:13','2015-12-22 16:56:13','[vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_custom_heading text=\"Buying Properties\" font_container=\"tag:h2|text_align:left\" google_fonts=\"font_family:Abril%20Fatface%3Aregular|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text css_animation=\"top-to-bottom\"]In Andhra Pradesh we are well-known real estate consultancy. Our team supports the clients to making property investments in any locations in Andhra Pradesh. We are having property database in huge numbers. You just give us your complete information about the requirement like what kind of property you want and of what will be the size and in which location, etc.\r\n\r\nWe would access our extensive database and immediately find a suitable property for you. We would also help you in negotiating the price and help with other aspects of the transaction. Buying Properties in Andhra Pradesh is easy now! Our services cover various residential, commercial, industrial and agricultural properties.\r\n<h1>Buying a home - step by step guide</h1>\r\n<span class=\"introText\"> Find out the process you need to follow when buying a home, including working out your budget and applying for a mortgage. You can also get help to buy a property, through affordable home ownership schemes.</span>\r\n<h2>A home-buying checklist</h2>\r\nBuying a home typically takes around two to three months and there are a number of steps you will need to take. You need to decide what you’re looking for and where and think about what your needs are - for example:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>where you want to live</li>\r\n	<li>whether you want a flat, a detached, a semi-detached or terraced property</li>\r\n	<li>how many rooms you need and how big they need to be</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Decide on your budget</h2>\r\nThink about what you can afford to spend. You’ll need to budget and plan for:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>one-off costs, like a deposit and Stamp Duty</li>\r\n	<li>regular, ongoing costs, like mortgage payments, rates and utilities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFor a list of the different costs, see ‘Mortgages and buying property’.\r\n\r\nYou don’t need to make a full mortgage application until you’ve found a property you want to buy.\r\n<h2>Get finances in place</h2>\r\nIf you can’t afford to buy a home without borrowing money, you can apply for a mortgage. Most lenders will give you an idea of how much money they are willing to lend you, called a ‘mortgage or agreement in principle’.\r\n<h2>Find a suitable property</h2>\r\nThere are several ways to find a property. Most people use an estate agent, but you can also buy direct from the seller (a private sale) or at auction.\r\n<h2>Make an offer for the property</h2>\r\nOnce you’ve found a property, you’ll need to make an offer to the seller.\r\n<h2>Hire a solicitor</h2>\r\nYour solicitor will deal directly with those of the vendors or sellers and carries out the legal work involved in buying a property. The estate agent will ask both you and the vendors for details of the solicitors to be used for the buying and selling.\r\n<h2>Get the property surveyed</h2>\r\nOnce your offer is accepted, you should get the property checked for any defects in its condition that might affect the value.\r\n\r\nYour mortgage lender may need a separate valuation to confirm the value of the property.\r\n<h2>Apply for a mortgage</h2>\r\nIf you don’t have the money to buy the property outright, you’ll need to make a full application for a mortgage. You can find more information in the link below:\r\n<h2>Exchange contracts</h2>\r\nThe exchange of the contracts to buy the property is the point where the sale is legally binding.\r\n\r\nSolicitors for both sides will get the buyer and the seller to sign a contract. This says you agree to the terms of the sale and to buy the property. You and the seller must now stick to the terms of the contract or face going to court.\r\n\r\nThe contract will list items that are included in the sale or that you’ve agreed to buy such as electrical items or furniture.\r\n\r\nYou’ll usually need to pay a deposit of 10 per cent of the house price to the seller at this point.\r\n<h2>Pay for the property and move in</h2>\r\nAfter the final legal tasks are complete, your solicitor will arrange for your mortgage company to pay the rest of the money to the seller’s solicitor. When this is done, the house belongs to you and you can move in on the agreed date. This is called ‘completion’.\r\n<h3>Be prepared for unexpected delays</h3>\r\nIf you’re buying a property, you’ll often find yourself in a chain of people, all relying on selling their property to buy a new property. This means the property you want to buy may fall through for reasons outside your control.\r\n\r\nBe prepared to arrange alternative temporary accommodation if you have to move out of your property.\r\n<h2>Get help to buy a home</h2>\r\nHigh property prices have made it difficult for many people to afford to buy a home. There are a number of schemes aimed at helping. You can find out more in the link below:[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Buying Properties','','inherit','closed','closed','','44-revision-v1','','','2015-12-22 16:56:13','2015-12-22 16:56:13','',44,'http://caltechsoft.com/rankprop/44-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(320,1,'2015-12-22 17:02:17','2015-12-22 17:02:17','[vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_custom_heading text=\"Selling Properties\" font_container=\"tag:h2|text_align:left\" google_fonts=\"font_family:Abril%20Fatface%3Aregular|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text]If you want to selling any property in Andhra Pradesh? Our team will take care of your burden to selling your property we have well experience and dedicated team for selling risk. We have excellent marketing team and also we have liaisons with local real estate agents.\r\n\r\nWe are giving valuable services to the client include giving tips and advice to develop the property value, advertising the property, arranging property visits, negotiating the price, property value assessment, etc.\r\n\r\nWe are a best real estate consultant in Andhra Pradesh and we can quickly &amp; easily sell all type properties like residential, commercial, industrial and agricultural. You can reach us for Selling your valuable Property &amp; get the best price for it.\r\n<div class=\"title-row\">\r\n<h1>Selling your house</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"title-row\">\r\n<p class=\"page-description\">Selling your house or rental property is a big decision. Find out what’s involved and how to go about it.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"summary main-content ga-content-container\">\r\n<h2>What you need to know when selling</h2>\r\nYou\'ll need to:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>find a lawyer</li>\r\n	<li>select a licensed real estate agent (or know how to sell the property yourself)</li>\r\n	<li>decide on a selling price</li>\r\n	<li>know how to deal with offers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>You may need your tax details</strong>You may need to give your tax details (eg your New Zealand IRD number and taxpayer identification number) to your property lawyer or the person doing your conveyancing.\r\n\r\nYou don\'t need to provide these details if you\'re an NZ citizen (or have an NZ residence visa) and you\'re:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>selling your main home, and</li>\r\n	<li>living in NZ now.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>You may need to pay tax on any profit you make</strong>You may need to pay tax on any profit you make on a property\'s value when you sell it. If you\'ve owned your house for less than 2 years, you may need to pay tax unless:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>the house is your main home</li>\r\n	<li>you\'ve inherited the house, or</li>\r\n	<li>you now own it because of a relationship break-up.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Leaky home claims when you sell</h3>\r\nYour claim ends when you sell your house, but the new owners may be able to make their own claim.\r\n<h2>Ways to sell property</h2>\r\nYou can sell your house yourself or use a real estate agent.\r\n\r\n<a class=\"external\" href=\"http://www.cab.org.nz/vat/hle/ho/Pages/Otherwaystosellyourhouse.aspx\" rel=\"external\">Selling your house privately <i class=\"fa fa-external-link\"></i><span class=\"external-text\" title=\"External site link\">(external site link)</span></a>\r\n\r\nYou can sell by auction, tender or at an advertised price.\r\n\r\n<a class=\"external\" href=\"http://www.reaa.govt.nz/ForBuyersAndSellers/Differentmethodsofbuyingandsellingproperty/Pages/Differentmethodsofbuyingandsellingproperty.aspx\" rel=\"external\">Ways to sell property <i class=\"fa fa-external-link\"></i><span class=\"external-text\" title=\"External site link\">(external site link)</span></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Sale and purchase agreement</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"summary main-content ga-content-container\">\r\n\r\nThe sale and purchase agreement sets out what you\'ve agreed with the buyer about the house sale (eg the price, chattels to be included, settlement date).\r\n<h2 id=\"selling-your-rental-or-investment-property\">Selling your rental or investment property</h2>\r\n<h3>If your property is rented</h3>\r\nIf your property is rented, you must let your tenants know you\'re selling. You must also get their permission if you need to enter the house to take photographs or show people the property.\r\n\r\nYou may need to transfer the tenancy and the bond to the new owner or give your tenants notice to leave.\r\n<h3>Depreciation on rental property</h3>\r\nIf you\'ve claimed depreciation on your rental property in the past, you\'ll need to take it into account when you sell your property and include it in your tax return (IR3).\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Selling Properties','','inherit','closed','closed','','46-revision-v1','','','2015-12-22 17:02:17','2015-12-22 17:02:17','',46,'http://caltechsoft.com/rankprop/46-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(321,1,'2015-12-22 17:02:50','2015-12-22 17:02:50','[vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_custom_heading text=\"Selling Properties\" font_container=\"tag:h2|text_align:left\" google_fonts=\"font_family:Abril%20Fatface%3Aregular|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text css_animation=\"top-to-bottom\"]If you want to selling any property in Andhra Pradesh? Our team will take care of your burden to selling your property we have well experience and dedicated team for selling risk. We have excellent marketing team and also we have liaisons with local real estate agents.\r\n\r\nWe are giving valuable services to the client include giving tips and advice to develop the property value, advertising the property, arranging property visits, negotiating the price, property value assessment, etc.\r\n\r\nWe are a best real estate consultant in Andhra Pradesh and we can quickly &amp; easily sell all type properties like residential, commercial, industrial and agricultural. You can reach us for Selling your valuable Property &amp; get the best price for it.\r\n<div class=\"title-row\">\r\n<h1>Selling your house</h1>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"title-row\">\r\n<p class=\"page-description\">Selling yo